# AfterArtificial Ecosystem Manifest v2.0

**Master Vision:** `docs/AFTERARTIFICIAL_ECOSYSTEM_MASTER_VISION.md`  
**Manifest:** `docs/AFTER_ECOSYSTEM_MANIFEST.md`  
**Alignment:** `docs/MASTER_VISION_ALIGNMENT_2026.md`

**You are designing modules of one AI-powered Digital Operating System** —
not individual applications.

## Platform-first (ask on every feature)

> Should this belong to one application, or become a shared platform
> capability every future application can reuse?

Always prefer `after_*` platform capabilities when reasonable.

## Core philosophy (One…)

Identity · AI · Cloud · Subscription · Family · Calendar · Wallet ·
Notification Center · Search · Marketplace · Documents Library ·
Design Language · Engineering Standard · API Platform · Event Bus ·
Data Platform · Ecosystem

## Product-owned only

Business Domain · Feature Modules · Navigation · Permissions ·
AI Skills · Dashboard Widgets

Everything else is inherited. ≥90% platform reuse.

## Consumer spine

Garage · Health · Kids · Finance · Home · Travel · Pet · Sports · News ·
Games · Find · Documents · AI

Presence truth = **SuperFind**. Documents UX = **SuperDocuments** over
One Documents Library. **SuperAI** = thin shell over `after_ai` — never
a second runtime.

## Enterprise (canonical names)

Hospital (ref) · Airport · Maritime · Factory · Construction · Retail ·
**Education** (alias School) · Hotel · Restaurant · Logistics · Energy ·
Municipality · **Farm** (alias Agriculture)

## Admission filter

“Is this a fundamental life/industry domain people manage for years?”
If no → feature of an existing domain, not a new Super App.

Events for communication. One AI with ecosystem context. Secure
consumer ↔ enterprise interop. Scale: ≥100 apps, zero architecture forks.
